<html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/tips.css"></head><body><p><b>Install packages</b></p><p>IntelliJ IDEA provides a quick-fix that automatically installs the package you are trying to import: if, after the <span class="code_emphasis">import</span> keyword, you type a name of a package that is not currently available on your machine, a quick-fix suggests to either ignore the unresolved reference, or download and install the missing package.</p></body></html>